Given a circle with equation $x^2 + y^2 = 1994^2$ and a point $(2 \cdot 1994, 2 \cdot 1994)$ outside the circle, find the point $(a,b)$ where a tangent from $(2 \cdot 1994, 2 \cdot 1994)$ touches the circle. Compute the sum of the coordinates of the point of tangency, i.e., $a + b$. egin{tikzpicture}\draw (0,0) circle (2cm);\draw (2.8,2.8) -- (0.707,0.707);\draw (0,0) -- (0.707,0.707);\draw (0.6,0.8) rectangle (0.9,0.6);
ode at (0,0) [below left] {$(0,0)$};
ode at (2.8,2.8) [above right] {$(2r,2r)$};
ode at (0.707,0.707) [above right] {$(a,b)$};\end{tikzpicture}
